body: Good Variety I like having a variety of six flavors for my "pups". I think that they enjoy changing their mealtime flavors each night.  I will admit that the dogs have favorite flavors among the six choices in each shipment., but they eat each flavor ... some more eagerly than others.  I easily divide one pan of Cesars between the two dogs for each soft food meal.  (I also leave very small dry kibbled food out for my dogs all day.)  These moist foods are already pretty well cut up into small pieces that would be perfect for dogs of any size.  My "pups" are 13 and 15 years old and were toothless when I adopted them, so I have to be careful that I feed them foods that they can swallow without choking.  Because of that, I do use a Braun hand-held food chopper to grind the food up into even smaller pieces that they can easily and safely  swallow.  My dogs definitely prefer the Cesar food to the dry kibble food.  Each pan contains  100 grams (3.5 oz.) of food.  Half of the 36 pans of Cesars are meat, with a little bit of meat juice jell.  The other half of the pans are small pieces of thinly sliced meat in gravy.  With six flavors, the dogs don't have to eat the same flavor every day ... they get a variety during the week.  The box in which the Cesars food arrives is divided into six sections, each holding one variety of food.  This makes it easiy to use as a food storage device.  The pans and the foil covering are recyclable.  I run them through the dishwasher (top shelf only) before I toss them into the recycle bin.  I have a repeating subscription for the 36 tub Cesars box of dog food.  It is so nice to have the food arrive at my front door so that my supply is constantly refreshed with little efort on my part.
